00:59:06.480 --> 00:59:08.200
And he said, yes.

00:59:08.200 --> 00:59:12.580
It was John Cooke, Sr., it's
a letter, 1837, downstairs,

00:59:12.580 --> 00:59:18.620 position:56%
and the curators and the manuscript
collection have pulled that document

00:59:18.620 --> 00:59:21.570
out along with some other
documents so that we can go down

00:59:21.570 --> 00:59:23.690
and actually see them, alright?

00:59:23.690 --> 00:59:29.240
So what I have for you, Mr.
Evans, and for you, Mr. David,

00:59:29.240 --> 00:59:32.810
is a copy of one of the [pause] --

00:59:32.810 --> 00:59:37.390
a copy of one of the reports
that Thurgood Marshall made

00:59:37.390 --> 00:59:42.980
to the NAACP's legal defense
